last_episode_to_air.name: This Will All Pass, Part 2
last_episode_to_air.overview: Yu Beom is on trial for manipulating the murder of Ha Ju Won. Before the trial, Dam Dong suspects that Yu Beom will try to leave the country. He tells Jae Chan, who tells Woo Joo that they must a travel ban preventing Yu Beom from leaving. Meanwhile, Woo Tak decides to take a huge risk in order to help this trial be successful.

name: While You Were Sleeping
overview: Burdened with visions of the future in their dreams, a young woman and two men try to prevent horrible events before they actually happen.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Can tragedies be avoided if they can be foreseen? In life, we witness small and big events. What would happen if someone can foresee every single event?

tagline: That future, that time, that fate, can it be changed?

episodes.name: The Accident, Part 1
episodes.overview: Hong Joo's dreams always come true. She dreams of hugging a man whom she has never met and is shocked at her actions. On the night of Valentine's Day, she is worried about her mom and hurries home to see her. Jae Chan has a dream about Hong Joo. He feels that he must prevent the events of his dreams from actually happening and tries his best to make sure that the accident never happens.

episodes.name: The Dream, Part 1
episodes.overview: Jae Chan finds out that Hong Joo has precognitive dreams on a regular basis and visits her after dreaming of his younger brother, Seung Won, becoming a murderer. Meanwhile, So Yoon tries to kill her father to protect her mother, and Seung Won tries to stop her and help her out.

episodes.name: Secretly, Greatly, Part 1
episodes.overview: Jae Chan and Hong Joo meet before the situation becomes irreversible. Before things get ugly, Jae Chan gets to Seung Won, and Hong Joo improvises so that things turn out differently from her dream. Jae Chan tells Seung Won to stay out of trouble, but they only drift apart more.

episodes.name: Two Different Dreams, Part 1
episodes.overview: Woo Tak has a precognitive dream that shows Hong Joo getting injured. He brings Jae Chan along to where it actually happens, so Jae Chan is able to prevent the injury from happening. Woo Tak and Hong Joo have similar dreams, but they end in different conclusions. They call Jae Chan in order to lead to the result they hope for.

As Jae Chan, Woo Tak and she begin to alter the future by preventing the events from happening, Hong Joo gains hope that perhaps her fate isn't sealed. As a result, she decides to return to SBC as a reporter.

episodes.name: The Secret That Can't Be Told, Part 2
episodes.overview: Jae Chan arrives to the scene of the crime to find out Woo Tak has been stabbed. He goes after Dae Hee and manages to arrest him. Jae Chan works hard to make sure that Dae Hee is prosecuted for his crimes. Meanwhile, Woo Tak stays at Hong Joo's house while he recovers and asks both Hong Joo and Jae Chan for favors while he's there.

episodes.name: Pride and Prejudice, Part 1
episodes.overview: A murder case of Yoo Su Kyung, a former professional archer, occurs and Do Hak Young is pointed as the prime suspect. Hak Young is a friend of Woo Tak, so Woo Tak convinces Hak Young to turn himself in. Jae Chan has to prosecute Hak Young, but there’s not enough evidence to do so.

episodes.name: A Boy Meets a Girl, Part 1
episodes.overview: Jae Chan gets shot by Yoo Su Kyung’s father, Yoo Man Ho, and gets transferred to a hospital. Hong Joo receives a note that Jae Chan sent to her before the accident and realizes that they’ve known each other for over 13 years.

episodes.overview: Jae Chan gets shot by Yoo Su Kyung’s father, Yoo Man Ho, and gets transferred to a hospital. Hong Joo receives a note that Jae Chan sent to her before the accident and realizes that they’ve known each other for over 13 years.

episodes.name: To Die or to be Bad, Part 1
episodes.overview: Jae Chan is released from the hospital and stays with Hong Joo for two days. Woo Tak and Hong Joo both dream about Jae Chan. In their dream, Jae Chan is in charge of a case that results in his resignation from the prosecution. Upon his return to work, Jae Chan must decide whether or not he will authorize the autopsy for a man who is set to donate his organs.

episodes.name: What Caused His Death? Part 1
episodes.overview: Jae Chan charges Moon Tae Min for murder despite everyone’s disapproval. He has to prove that Lee Hwan didn’t die from the organ transplant, but Yu Beom has a strong argument that Jae Chan can’t win over. Meanwhile, Moon Sun wants to keep Jae Chan away from Hong Joo because she doesn’t want to see Hong Joo suffer.

episodes.name: We're on Our Way to Meet You Now, Part 1
episodes.overview: Woo Tak and Jae Chan share their theory behind why they can see each other's future in their dreams. Hong Joo goes to Criminal Division Three to follow a prosecutor for three days for an article, and Jae Chan is worried that he will embarrass himself in front of her. Meanwhile, a cellphone thief provides evidence for a past case.

episodes.overview: After the arson, Criminal Division Three is swamped with work. Woo Joo and Hee Min look into the arson case, and Ji Gwang and Jae Chan reinvestigate the IV drip serial murder case. Hong Joo also begins to look into the case. Meanwhile, Yu Beom receives a mysterious text message from the real killer.
